text.section:
For each license for which an applicant applies, the applicant shall:
Submit a separate application;
Pay a separate nonrefundable license fee;
Pay any application processing fee or other fees that the Nationwide Mortgage Licensing System and Registry imposes in connection with the application;
If applicable, pay the surcharge; and
File a separate surety bond or other financial guaranty under § 11-508 of this subtitle.
